text: Peter Eneji Moses (born 8 April 1999) is a Nigerian international footballer who plays for Slovak club FK Senica, as a striker. ==Career== He has played club football for Plateau United, Akwa United and FK Senica. He signed for FK Senica in July 2019. He scored on his debut for the club later that month, coming off the substitutes' bench to score 2 goals.
